  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (b192af4 2022-05-30T00:08:26.00382Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge script -h\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n## visible_alias\r\n- make alias visible in help text \r\n\r\n```sh\r\nforge script -h\r\n\r\n\r\n--hardhat                    Use the Hardhat-style project layout. [aliases: hh]\r\n-f, --fork-url <URL>               Fetch state over a remote endpoint instead of starting from an empty state [aliases: rpc-url]\r\n--target-contract <CONTRACT_NAME>    The name of the contract you want to run [aliases: tc]\r\n```\r\n\r\n## value_name\r\n- explicit value names, mostly plural of regular wallet options\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nforge script -h\r\n\r\n    -s, --sig <SIGNATURE>                    The signature of the function you want to call in the contract, or raw calldata [default: run()]\r\n```\r\n\r\npr below",
